re. High humidity levels in bathrooms can lead to the growth of mold and mildew, which can damage structures and create an unhealthy environment. Drying systems in bathrooms help control moisture by regulating air circulation, temperature, and humidity. These systems are often integrated into ventilation systems to maintain a dry and comfortable environment, particularly in regions with high levels of humidity, such as coastal areas in Mexico.</p> <p>In Mexico, where both residential and tourism industries are flourishing, there is a growing demand for high-quality bathroom drying solutions. The use of energy-efficient drying control systems is gaining traction as part of efforts to reduce energy consumption and improve indoor air quality. With technological advancements, systems can now be designed to be more compact and efficient, providing a quieter operation and faster drying capabilities. This makes bathroom drying systems an increasingly popular choice for new constructions and renovations, contributing to the growing market for drying control systems in this application.</p> <h2>Others</h2> <p>The "Others" category includes various unique applications of drying control systems in industries such as pharmaceuticals, electronics, and automotive manufacturing. In these industries, moisture control is crucial to ensure the integrity and functionality of products. For instance, in the pharmaceutical industry, drying systems are used to preserve the quality of active ingredients and maintain proper storage conditions for drugs. Similarly, in the electronics industry, moisture control is essential to prevent damage to sensitive components during manufacturing and storage.</p> <p>As technological advancements continue to drive innovation in drying control systems, the "Others" segment is becoming more diverse. In Mexico, industries such as pharmaceuticals and electronics are seeing increased demand for precision drying solutions to meet international standards and en